      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the rationale is, if bbagent is interrupted (e.g. user cancels the build and swarming task get cancelled), once luciexe/recipe exits, we want to use all the remaining time to stream the logs before bbagent gets killed (receive SIGKILL from swarming). So that those logs will be available in logdog instead of die with bbagent.\n\nI think I can remove it, because SIGKILL would definitely arrive before wait is over. In theory, it will be at most 500ms before receiving SIGKILL and wait is guaranteed larger than that.",
      "parentUuid": "7a83f794_36a614a4",
